Mike Brown had marijuana in his system. That changes nothing.
Three different autopsies have been or are being conducted on the body of Michael Brown, the unarmed black teenager who was shot by police in Ferguson, MO on August 9th. The first of them was the autopsy conducted by St. Louis County — the jurisdiction conducting the criminal investigation into Brown's death, to see if Officer Darren Wilson should be charged with a crime. It included a toxicology test, which can only be done once. This doesn't tell us much. There's   between marijuana use and aggression (and even if there was, a general link wouldn't tell us about a specific case like this one). Moreover, t Get our newsletter in your inbox twice a week. 